<TITLE> Rain plays foul at Grenada </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)  Rain prevented any play after tea on the third day of the second and final Test between West Indies and Bangladesh at St George's, Grenada on Saturday. The home side were only 197 ahead with two wickets remaining as they ended a miserable day on 192 for eight at the National Cricket Stadium. Lower-order batsman David Bernard was holding the innings together with a gritty knock of 61 off 71 balls that contained six fours and a six. Earlier, West Indies, who resumed after lunch on 124-5, lost Darren Sammy for 22 after he was caught at short midwicket off the bowling of Enamul Haque Jr. It ended a threatening 56-run stand with Bernard. One run later, Shakib Al Hasan made it a double breakthrough when he had Chadwick Walton (1) caught at second slip. Ryan Austin fell for three just before tea after adding 20 runs for the eighth wicket. The batsman had a rush of blood and only managed to top edge the ball from Shahadat Hossain to Tamim Iqbal running backwards from short mi
